  "text": "The hot restart mechanism in Envoy v1.31.2 is implemented across multiple C++ source files in the envoyproxy/envoy repository. The architecture follows a parent-child process model with Unix domain socket communication.\n\n## Core Components:\n\n1. **HotRestart Interface** (envoy/server/hot_restart.h): Defines the abstract interface for hot restart operations including draining parent listeners, duplicating parent listen sockets, handling UDP forwarding, managing admin shutdown, and stats merging.\n\n2. **HotRestartImpl** (source/server/hot_restart_impl.{h,cc}): The main implementation that manages shared memory segments (SharedMemory struct) and coordinates between parent and child processes through HotRestartingParent and HotRestartingChild instances. It handles shared memory initialization with process-shared mutexes for logging and access log synchronization.\n\n3. **Parent Process Handler** (source/server/hot_restarting_parent.{h,cc}): Implements the parent side of the hot restart protocol. Creates and binds Unix domain sockets, listens for child process requests via onSocketEvent(), handles socket file descriptor passing through getListenSocketsForChild(), implements listener draining via drainListeners(), manages admin shutdown, and exports stats to the child.\n\n4. **Child Process Handler** (source/server/hot_restarting_child.{h,cc}): Implements the child side that initiates requests to the parent. Handles socket duplication from the parent, registers UDP forwarding listeners, manages parent drain callbacks through ParentDrainedCallbackRegistrar, requests parent stats, and initiates parent termination.\n\n5. **RPC Protocol Base** (source/server/hot_restarting_base.{h,cc}): Implements the core Unix domain socket communication protocol via RpcStream class. Manages datagram socket creation/binding, message serialization/deserialization using protobuf, and handles multi-datagram message fragmentation (max 4096 bytes per datagram). Supports separate channels for main RPC and UDP packet forwarding to prevent interference.\n\n6. **Protocol Definition** (source/server/hot_restart.proto): Defines HotRestartMessage protocol with Request and Reply message types including PassListenSocket, ShutdownAdmin, Stats, DrainListeners, Terminate, and ForwardedUdpPacket.\n\n7. **OS System Calls** (envoy/api/os_sys_calls_hot_restart.h, source/common/api/posix/os_sys_calls_impl_hot_restart.{h,cc}): Abstracts POSIX shared memory operations (shm_open, shm_unlink) for creating and managing the hot restart shared memory segment.\n\n8. **No-Op Implementation** (source/server/hot_restart_nop_impl.h): Provides a no-operation implementation for platforms or configurations that don't support hot restart.\n\n## Key Features Implemented:\n\n- **Parent-Child Handshake**: Unix domain socket-based RPC protocol for parent-child communication\n- **Socket Passing**: File descriptor passing via ancillary data (CMSG) to transfer listening sockets from parent to child\n- **Drain Sequence**: Parent listeners gracefully drain connections while child handles new connections; UDP forwarding allows parent to forward unrecognized QUIC packets to child\n- **Child Readiness**: Parent drained callbacks register with listeners to pause UDP listeners until parent is drained\n- **Shared Memory**: Version-checked shared memory segment maintains compatibility and process-shared mutexes for synchronized logging\n- **Stats Merging**: Parent stats exported to child with delta tracking for accurate cumulative statistics across restarts\n"
}

